<br>
Please privde a link.<br>
<br>
I have found NO reports of magicians soloing planar mobs with the new fire pet. It only exists on Test and the number of high-level magicians on Test is rather low, so it is not too surprising that first-hand reports may be rare. I'd like to read one, so please prive a reference to back up your claim.<br>
<br>
It may not matter too much. *I* can solo planar mobs with my air pet today! (And possibly earth pet, hehe, have to give that a try.)<br>
<br>
I may have to post a rant about the concept of &quot;signature spells&quot; because it seems kind of short-sighted to me. Classes are not defined by spells, but by abilities. That is amply demonstrated by so-called &quot;signature spells&quot; being found on items equipable by other classes, and the fact that many classes share the same spells, but in slightly different ways. For instance, beastlords get many of the same spells shaman do, but at a later level. Shaman and enchanters both get slow and haste, but each one is slightly better at one than the other. Wizards and magicians both get DD spells, but wizards consistently get better, more efficient DD spells than magicians. (For the record, mages do not consider CotH to be a &quot;signature spell.&quot; Some consider it a nuisance, heh.)<br>
<br>
Even if we allow that Ice Comet is a wizard spell, giving it to the wizard pet makes sense, just as giving it to NPC wizards makes sense. I love fighting wizard frogs in Seb. They spend all their time casting. Sure, when they cast Ice Comet and it lands on me, it hurts! But it rarely lands because my pet keeps interrupting its casting, hehe. The point is that NPCs cast Ice Comet, not that wizards are fun to fight. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nueelien>nueelien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Thermonuclear Warlord</span><br>  Posts: 573<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/22/03 10:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A serious concern</span><hr size=1> Taken from the mage boards<br>
