<br>
Currently the level 49 fire pet is more useful that either of the standard fire pets we receive between 50-60 (don't know about the 60+ one... but from what I've been told it's more of the same). I can count the number of times I've ever casted the fire pet spells in question on no hands... since I've casted it absolutely zero times (other than testing it to see what it does/doesn't do in a safe environment). As having pets is one of the main reasons we mages exist and can out DPS most classes it only makes sense to look at ways to fix a problem which renders a pet useless. <br>
<br>
Are the current changes on the test server for fire pets going to wreck the game and make wizards superfluous (big word of the day... heh)? I doubt it. The spells that these fire pets cast are limited by the pet's low mana level (as I've heard it, much lower than an PC of the same level... even though reclaiming and recasting a new fire pet may mitigate this somewhat), spell selection (we don't get to pick which spells are being cast... hopefully the right ones at the right time, but how many NPC's still cast the wrong spell at the wrong time?) and general usefulness. The mobs I'm hitting at the level I would obtain these pets often resists these spells (even if Malaised), and generally not add to my DPS as a fire shielded air/water/earth pet could... or even a spell such as Dyzil's Deafening Decoy. In a solo situation the new fire pets are still useless... an earth pet which roots most mobs for my level or an air pet which stuns mobs are much more useful. <br>
<br>
The way I've interpreted your comments Faramir is that you're more upset that mages get to cast a pet which infringes upon trademark spells which wizards have. So should rogues be upset that our water pet can backstab? Monks and Barbs/Trolls/Ogres because our air pets can stun? The powers that be in SoE have decreed that our mage pets above the 50th level take on the characteristics of specific classes. They also decided that fire pets are the equivalent of wizards. If you don't like the fire pets casting wizard spells... how about you petition them to make fire pets into enchanters... I'd love a pet who could provide some crowd control (/rofl). <br>
<br>
Bottom line is that SoE is trying to make fire pets more useful to mages who currently find zero use for them. Whether all the changes implemented on the test server make it to the live servers remains to be seen... that is why it is called the test server. But I say good on SoE for at least trying to find a way to make our fire pets more useful to us. <br>
<br>
And don't worry Faramir... I will throw over my new and improved fire pet for a proper wizard to hunt with any day... and I can't think of any one who would think that this pet could ever take over the role of a wizard (unless my pet could  evac me.... hmmm... time for me to go send in some feedback to SoE... hehe).<br>
<br>
Utno<br>
