<br>
The water pet only has the rogues backstab. The Earth bashes like a warrior, air fights like a monk. But they each only get a small percentage of those classes abilites. Water doesn't get instill doubt, or any of the other rogue abilites. Same with air. It doesn't have FD incase it's losing. <br>
<br>
But the test fire pet has almost every non porting spell the wizard gets between levels 49-52. Every stun, root, nuke, area effect, snare and shield and damage shield. That's alot. That's is what a wizard is when it comes to fighting. <br>
<br>
So not only does it get our absorb damage shield spell, it gets whatever the mage casts on it, it gets our nukes, our roots and snares <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>and</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> it's melee abilities and it's own elemental burst attack, which I believe doesn't require mana. It's a level 52 wizard with 2500 hit points. <br>
<br>
If it's is casting Tishan's discord Atol's shackles, well, those are quest or npc dropped spells. Atol's drops through out Kunark, and Tishan's you get for handing over 1 of four different spells. <br>
<br>
